Hi [~apitrou], thanks for the update. I uninstalled the icc, gcc stepped in and it worked. But now I have this new error when I use the read_parquet() function call.

 
{code:java}
Error: IOError: NotImplemented: Support for codec 'snappy' not built{code}
 

And I don't have root permissions to install libsnappy-dev. Compiling the source for that lib and making symlinks will be too tedious to resolve any possible dependencies. This idea was suggested [here|https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/73653/installing-a-package-locally-to-a-user-best-practices]

 

Thanks for your help. I will close this issue for now.
